#N canvas 646 23 548 855 10;
#X obj 21 18 uoscil/wander~;
#X text 114 18 RANDOM WANDERING VALUE WITH GRAVITATIONAL PULL;
#X text 18 48 Generates a wandering value between -1 and 1 \, tending
towards 0 A weighted random chance is used to keep the value centred
around 0 \; at 1 there is a 100% chance to go down \, at -1 100% chance
to go up \; and at 0 there is a 50/50 chance to go either up or down.
;
#X text 18 128 There is an optional exponential scaling factor to the
weighted chance (set on creation) \, i.e. the weights increase exponentially
instead of linearly as the value approaches the extremes. Lower exponents
will make the value stick more to 0 and higher exponents the opposite.
;
#N canvas 0 22 450 278 (subpatch) 0;
#X array \$0-graph_1 1000 float 3;
